laboratory_examinations.findings: Biopsy findings of a fresh papule showed thick epidermis and abundant calcium deposition, compared to initial biopsy findings before treatment with vitamin D3. Electron microscopy revealed electron-lucent areas suggesting unusual mineralization.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: More abundant calcium deposition than before therapy.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Serum levels of calcium were within the normal range.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Neither calcium nor phosphorus serum levels were increased.
